county_zips <- read.csv('county-zips.csv', header = T) %>% rename(zip = Zip) %>% mutate(zip = as.character(zip))
historical <- read.csv('historical_initial.csv', header = T)
info <- read.csv('info_initial.csv', header = T)
h <- historical %>%
  separate(address, sep = ', ', into = c("street","city","statezip")) %>%
  separate(statezip, sep = ' ', into = c('state','zip')) %>%
  separate(Price, sep = " ", into = c("price", NA))
## Warning: Expected 2 pieces. Missing pieces filled with `NA` in 23 rows [5, 6,
## 39, 107, 126, 127, 141, 146, 169, 170, 236, 505, 506, 847, 848, 959, 998, 1089,
## 1152, 1160, ...].
i <- info %>% separate(address, sep = ', ', into = c("street","city","statezip")) %>% separate(statezip, sep = ' ', into = c('state','zip'))
i <- i %>% filter(beds > 0 & baths > 0) %>% select(link:sqft & !'list_price')
h <- h %>% select(street:price)
sold <- h %>% filter(Event == "Sold")
list <- h %>% filter(Event == "Listed for sale")
change <- historical %>% filter(Event == "Price change") %>% separate(Price, sep = " ", into = c("to","pct"))
sold_info <- sold %>%
  left_join(i, by = c("street","city","state","zip"))

si <- sold_info %>%
  filter(complete.cases(sold_info)) %>%
  left_join(county_zips, by = 'zip') %>%
  relocate(Date, .before = street) %>%
  relocate(..County, .before = street) %>%
  mutate(Date = yearmonth(mdy(Date)), price = as.numeric(str_replace_all(price, "[[$,]]",""))) 

colnames(si)[2] <- "County"
si %>% filter(complete.cases(si)) %>%
  group_by(Date, County) %>%
  summarise(mean_sale = mean(price)) %>%
  as_tsibble(index = Date, key = County) %>%
  autoplot() + xlab("Date of Sale") + ylab("Mean Sale Price") + ggtitle("Monthly Mean Sale Price, All Homes, By County")

Exponential Smoothing Model

Exponential Smoothing Models aim to explain trend & seasonality in the TS (both of which are present in our data)

msales_median <- si %>% filter(complete.cases(si)) %>% group_by(Date) %>% summarise(median_sale = median(price)) %>% as_tsibble() %>% fill_gaps(median_sale = 0)
## Using `Date` as index variable.
msales_median %>% autoplot()
## Plot variable not specified, automatically selected `.vars = median_sale`

msales_dcomp_add <- msales_median %>% model(classical_decomposition(median_sale, type = "additive")) %>% components() %>% autoplot()
msales_dcomp_mult <- msales_median %>% model(classical_decomposition(median_sale, type = "multiplicative")) %>% components() %>% autoplot()
msales_dcomp_x11 <- msales_median %>% model(x11 = X_13ARIMA_SEATS(median_sale ~ x11())) %>%
  components() %>% autoplot()
msales_dcomp_stl <- msales_median %>% model(stl = STL(median_sale)) %>%
  components() %>% autoplot()
msales_dcomp_add

library(leaps)
ts <- si %>% filter(complete.cases(si)) %>% group_by(Date) %>% summarise(median_sqft = median(sqft), median_price = median(price), median_baths = median(baths), median_beds = median(beds)) %>% as_tsibble() %>% fill_gaps(median_sqft = 0, median_price = 0, median_baths = 0, median_beds = 0)
## Using `Date` as index variable.
autoplot(ts, median_price)

subset <- regsubsets(median_price ~ median_beds + median_baths + median_sqft + median_beds:median_baths + median_beds:median_sqft + median_baths:median_sqft, data = ts)
plot(subset, scale = "Cp")

model_best <- lm(median_price ~ median_sqft + median_beds:median_baths + median_beds:median_sqft, data = ts)
AIC(model_best)

fit_nick <- ts %>%
  model(TSLM(median_price ~ median_sqft + median_beds:median_baths + median_beds:median_sqft))
report(fit_nick)
